main event: A radar observer reported a lighted aircraft of unconventional design over Tokyo, Japan, on 26 March 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as white and elliptical-shaped with blinking lights., The sighting was reported by a radar observer at Dainamasu Air Force Base., The radar blip was observed at 1207 and faded by 1230., There were additional objects tracked in proximity during various sightings., The radar recording suggested the object maintained a steady speed.
witnesses: radar observer at Dainamasu AF Base
